column2: Slight hazy sun.  1 1/2" of rain the last two nights.
Hazy- 10% clouds.  N wind 5-10 mph. 1" rain on 8/4. air 75 degrees.  Water temp. 76 degrees.
5% clouds- wind 10 mph.- 80 degrees.  5" rain in last 2 weeks. Water temp. 76 degrees.
5% clouds- wind 5 mph- 78 degrees.  Water temp. 76 degrees.
5% clouds- wind 5 mph- 75 degrees.  Water temp. 74 degrees.
40% clouds- wind 15 mph- 65 degrees. water temp. 68 degrees.
30% clouds wind 5 mph. 60 degrees. water temp. 60 degrees.
Clear sky. calm. sunny. 70 F. 1 pair loons arrived 3 weeks ago. no boat traffic yet. water temp 64 F.
Partly cloudy. wind approx. 12 mph.  Air temp 68 F. 1 pair loons. not a lot of boat traffic. water temp 62 F.
Clear sky. some small clouds. air temp 72 F. winds 5 mph. water temp 68 F.
More than average boat traffic.  Very little wind. air temp 78 F. many people enjoying the lake this week. water temp 74 F.
Unusually hot (86 F) and humid (80%) day.  Dew point 72. 5 mph wind.  Sunny.  Several loons + ducks.  No boat traffic. clear. water temp 84 F.
Air temp 70 F.  50% clouds.  Windy (12 mph).  Geese are flocking.  It's been a very warm summer. water temp 74 F.
Air temp 60 F.  Wind 8 mph.  Clear skies. adult loons are gone.  Geese flocking.  Very little boat traffic. water temp 64 F.
20% clouds.  Air temp 64 F.  Winds @ 5 mph.  No boat traffic. Baby loons still on lake. Water temp 56 F.
Partly cloudy skies- no traffic on lake yet- air temperature is 85 degrees- water temperature is 60 degrees- loons arrived on 4/4- and saw baby geese.
50% clouds- slight breeze- air temperature is 65 degrees- water temperature is 72 degrees- few people on lake- and baby ducks and geese around.
10% cloud cover- 5 mph breeze- air temperature is 80 degrees- water temperature is 76 degrees- only one loon seen lately- and had 8" of rain on 7/8.
40% cloud cover- loons did not breed this year- too many jet skies- water temperature is 78 degrees- and air temperature is 84 degrees.
Windy - 10 mph- 20% cloud cover- air temperature is 70 degrees- water temperature is 70 degrees- and don't see any baby loons.

Clear sky- wind 7 mph- water temperature is 66 degrees- air temperature is 64 degrees- and lots of scum on lake today. it's been windy this year.  Loons have stopped having babies on our lake- lots of boat traffic this year- drive very close to shoreline.
Air temp 70 F- Water temp 65 F.  15% cloud cover.  Very little traffic on lake.
Air temp 75 F.  Water temp 68 F.  Still not a lot of lake traffic.  25% clouds.  5 mph breeze.
High boat traffic.  More boats on lake than in previous years - increased jet skis.  Loons not mating.  Air temp 78 F.  Water temp 74 F.
Air temp 85 F.  Water temp 78 F.  Partly cloudy.  No breeze.  A lot of boat traffic.  3 new homes on lake.
Partly cloudy- breezy.  Air temp 50 F.  Water temp 50 F.  Geese flocking.  Migratory birds on lake.
Air temperature is 65 degrees- water temperature is 62 degrees- slight breeze- partly cloudy- and no traffic on lake yet.
Air temperature is 70 degrees- water temperature is 70 degrees- clear sky- not a lot of lake traffic yet - it's been too cool.
Air temperature is 65 degrees- water temperature is 78 degrees- breezy at 5 mph- partly cloudy- no breeding loons- too much traffic.
Water temperature is 78 degrees- air temperature is 90 degrees- partly cloudy- 7 mph breeze- very hot August and rainy- much boat traffic.
Air temperature is 82 degrees- water temperature is 75 degrees- partly cloudy- slight breeze- and lots of rain this year - above average.
Millions of freshwater jellyfish in the water.  Sunny- no wind.  No boats.  Water temp 64 F.  Air temp 70 F.  Beautiful day.
No wind. Broken clouds with some sun. No wind.  No boats.  Water temp 56 F.  All the jellyfish are gone.
Wind 10 mph out of West.  Ice out of lake on 0423.  Air temp is 55.  Surface water temp is 55.  Two loons are back again this year.
Sunny- ligth clouds and wind about 10 mph.  Has been raining for two weeks and lake has risen about 2.5 inches over that time.  No boat traffic.
Bright- sunny day with light breeze.  Lake has a lot of the yellow floating debris from the trees.  We have only seen one loon for the last several days now.
Bright sunny day- clear sky- wind 10-15 mph- no boats.  2 loons plus their recent baby loon.
Clear day- very light breeze.  No boat traffic.  Baby loon still on the back of its mother.
Very light breeze.  Bright- sunny day.  No boat traffic.  Baby loon is growing quite fast considering its very late start.
Bright sunny day.  Wind about 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  All 3 loons close by.
Clear day- no wind- no boats. Young loon getting bigger. Clear day- no wind- no boats. Young loon getting bigger.
Sunny day- light breeze- no boat traffic.  Two baby loons still on the lake.

Gray and overcast.  Light wind.  No boat traffic.  Two baby loons still on the lake.  Very small fresh water jellyfish seen on west end of lake about 2 feet under the surface.  About the diameter of a little finger.
Bright day.  Light breeze.  No boat traffic.   No jellyfish to be seen anywhere on the lake.  Both baby loons are still present.  this will be the last entry for the year.
Partly cloudy- wind about 10 mph.  Water temp at 51 F.  Both loons on the the water.  Two eagles soaring also.
Sunny with wispy clouds. Wind from the west around 10 mph.  Ice out this year on April 7th.  Water temp at 59 F.  Both loons on the water.

Bright sunny cloudless day with wind abut 10 mph out of the southwest.  Surface temp of the water is 62 F.  2 loons on the water.  No boat traffic.  When testing the secchi- I had to extend all of the line plus most of my arm and could still see the disk clearly.  Recorded at 30+ feet!  I have never seen the water better than this.
Sunny- clear with light wind around 8 mph.  More boat traffic than normal.  Surface water temp at 62 F.  Two loons on the water.
Partly cloudy and light wind from west around 10 mph.  One loon on the water.  Lake has a lot of the yellow particles from the pine trees on it and the water is noticeably greenish.  No boat traffic.
Bright sunshine- a few wispy clouds.  Light breeze out of the west around 5 mph.  One loon on the water.  A little boat traffic.
Beautiful sunny day.  Light wind of 5-7 mph.  Two loons on the water.  No sign of a baby loon.  No boat traffic.

column1: Cool and overcast.  Light wind about 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  Two loons on the water.  Surface water temperature at 67 F.

column2: Bright sunny day.  Very light breeze.  Two loons on the water.  No boat traffic.
Sunny skies with light puffy clouds.  Wind at 5 to 7 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the area.
Overcast with a light wind around 8 to 10 mph.  Both loons present.
Sunny days with light clouds.  Wind light around 4-5 mph.  No boat traffic.  Both loons present.
Bright sunshine.  No wind.  No boat traffic.  Water surface temp 72 F.  Two loons on the lake.
Sunny day with wind between 5 and 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  Two loons in the area.
Bringt sunny day.  Wind at about 5 mph.  No boats.  No loons around.  Water surface temp at 71 F.
Clear day- light wind around 5 to 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  The loons have left.  Looked to see if freshwater jellyfish present but did not see any.
First reading for 2010.  Ice out very early this year -- March 28th.  Bright sunny day- no clouds- slight breeze 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  Have heard the loons but have not seen them on the lake yet.
Sunny day with winds around 15 mph.  Very little boat traffic.  Water surface temp at 55 F  No loons to be seen today.
Beautiful clear day.  No clouds- no wind and bright sunshine.  No boat traffic.  One loon on the lake.
Beautiful sunny day.  Wispy clouds and a very light breeze at about 3 mph.  Small amount of boat traffic.  No loons visible.  The surface of the lake is warming up.
Overcast with sprinkles of rain.  Wind around 5 mph  This is the first satellite day but it will probably be too cloudy for a reading.  No boat traffic.  The loon is on the nest.
Beautiful day for testing.  Bright sunshine- wispy clouds and almost no breeze.  No boat traffic.  The loon is still on her nest and has been there for most of the month.

Beautiful day- 83 degrees with a breeze around 10-12 mph.  Bright and sunny with no clouds.  Some boat traffic.  The loon pair had one baby loon.  Born on June 29.  Unfortunately it disappeared two days later.
Beautiful clear day- bright and sunny- no clouds- and not a breeze.  No boat traffic.  Three loons on the lake.
Beautiful sunny day.  Light breeze from the southwest at 5 mph.  Blue sky with a few puffy clouds.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the area.
Beautiful clear day- no clouds- light breeze at 5 to 8 mph.  Some boat traffic.  No loons to be seen.
Clear skies- light breeze at 3-5 mph.  No traffic- and one immature loon on the lake.
Beautiful day.  Bright sunshine- no clouds in the sky.  71 degrees.  Wind about 5 mph from the southwest.  No boat traffic.  No loons on the lake.
Beautiful fall day. Bright sun- no clouds- no wind.  No boat traffic.  This will be my last entry for 2010.

First testing for 2011.  Ice out late- on April 12th.  Water up over fall of last year.  This year we will also be sampling for chlorophyll and phosphorus.  Two loons on the lake.  They were late in coming also.  Sunny day with breeze about 10 mph.  Temperature in the 60's.
Sunny with puffy clouds but wind in excess of 15 mph.  No boat traffic.  Saw one loon this morning- but have seen three together on the lake the past week.
Beautiful sunny day with scattered clouds.  Wind around 12-15 mph.  Small amount of boat traffic.
Sunny day with puffy white clouds.  Wind out of the east around 7-8 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the area.
Nice day- partially sunny and winds around 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  Two loons onthe water.
Bringt sunny day.  No wind- no boat traffic.  Two loons on the lake.
Bright sunshine with winds about 10 mph.  No loons seen today but a pair is back and hopefully preparing a nest.  No boat traffic.

Bright sunny hot day. Wind at 10-15 mph when I started sampling but was 25 mph+ by the time I was done.  Considerable boat traffic.  Two loons present since their failed nesting attempt ended near the end of May.
Sunny- warm day with some thin clouds. Wind at 5 mph.  Some boat traffic.  No loons seen on the lake today.
Bright sunny morning.  No clouds and wind around 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons in sight but can hear them calling periodically.
Bright clear day.  Some boat traffic.  Slight breeze.  Two loons in the area.
Beautiful sunny day with a clear sky.  Winds arund 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the area.
Partly cloudy- slight breeze.  Boat traffic present.
Cloudless bright day.  Breeze from northwest around 7 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the area.  Very small (3/8") freshwater jellyfish can be seen in the lake.
First test of the year.  Ice out on May 2nd.  Bright s;unny afternoon.  Light breeze.  One loon heard on lake on May 5th.  Two loons on lake today.
Overcast morning.  Very little breeze.  No boat traffic.
Sunny afternoon with partial clouds.  Light breeze around 5 mph.  Some boat traffic.  Two loons on the lake after a failed nesting attempt.
Bright sunny late afternoon.  No clouds.  Very light breeze.  Lot of boat traffic.
Blue sky and puffy white clouds in the late afternoon.  Wind around 8-10 mph.  Some boat traffic.  3 loons together on the lake.
Bright clear afternoon.  No clouds and no breeze.  No boat traffic.  One loon on the lake.  The lake has dropped 12.5 inches from its high in the spring.
Sunny afternoon.  Clear skies- Wind arund 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  Loons are gone.  This will be the last entry for 2013.

The ice went out of Lake Viola on April 28th.  The day is partly cloudy with winds around 10 mph.  2 loons are on the lake but haven't shown any indication of nesting yet.  No boat traffic.  Temperature data missing as my temperature monitor needs replacing.
Bright sunny day. Winds around 8 to 10 mph.  Some boat traffic.
Totally overcast.  Light breeze at 5 mph. No boat traffic.
Completely overcast.  Wind about 5-8 mph.  A little boat traffic.  No loons in the area.
Beautiful clear day with bright sunshine.  Winds at 2-5 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons present on the lake.
Most cloudy with light wind around 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons.  This will be the last testing of Lake Viola for 2014.
Clear blue sky.  Wind around 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons.  Beautiful day.
Beautiful clear day.  Light breeze.  The pine pollen that was all over the lake is pretty well gone and the lake is much clearer.  No boat traffic.
Clear bright day- no clouds.  A light breeze- 2-3 mph.  No boat traffic.  6 loons on the lake -- 2 parents with 2 new chicks- and two under younger birds on the other end of the lake.
Clear evening. Bright sunshine with no wind. No boat traffic. Two adult loons plus one chick.
Partly cloudy.  Winds around 6 mph. No boat traffic.  Two loons plus chick on west end and two single loons on east end of lake.
Cloudy day with breeze around 5 mph.  No traffic.  Loon and chick on the lake.
Clear sunny day with light breeze. No boat traffic. Loon and chick on the lake.

Partly sunny with breeze about 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  Freshwater jellyfish still suspended over deep water on west end.  Thermocline normally around 17 feet is gone- indicating lake is starting to mix. One loon adult and one chick still on the lake.
Partly cloudy day. Almost no wind. The freshwater jellyfish are still suspended over deep water.  No boat traffic.  Surface water temperature has dropped to 62 F.  One loon chick still on the lake.

This will be the last test for the year.  Bright sunny day. No wind. No boat traffic.  Surface temp down to 53 F.  Signs the lake is equalizing in temp.  The freshwater jellyfish are gone now.  No loons present.
First testing of the year.  Ice went out very early this year- on March 25th.  Two loons back on the lake April 4th.  Today is sunny- no clouds- and wind at about 10 mph.
Sunny day.  Light wind at around 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in sight.  Surface temp is now 54.5 F- up from 49 F two weeks ago.
Sunny day with almost no clouds.  Wind around 7 mph.  No boat traffic.  Two loons on the lake.
Bright sunny day with slight clouds.  Wind around 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons in sight.
Partly cloudy with wind around 7 or 8 mph.  Some boat traffic. One loon on east end of lake.
Bright sunny morning with light wispy clouds.  Breeze out of southeast around 5 mph.  Some boat traffic.  Two loons on lake.
Clear bright sunny day.  Wind around 5 mph.  A little boat traffic. Two loons on the lake.
Sunny day with puffy clouds.  Wind around 8 to 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  My temperature monitoring instrument stopped working so no temp by depth data.
Sunny evening.  No wind.  One loon in the area.  No boat traffic.
Beautiful clear day. No wind. Lake is like glass.  Some boat traffic.  One loon in the area.

Totally overcast day.  Wind 5-8 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons in the area.  The freshwater jellyfish showed up on the lake about two weeks ago.  Found them in deep water and also the shallow bay near the public launch.  No temperature readings as my temperature probe unit stopped working.
Bright sunny day.  No wind.  Water is like glass.  No boat traffic.  Loons are gone. Freshwater jellyfish are gone also.
Sunny day with light wispy clouds.  Breeze at 3 to 4 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons.  No jellyfish.  This will be the last entry for 2016.

First day of testing in 2017.  Ice out on March 28th.  Two loons back on lake on April 4th.  Today- sunny day with wispy clouds.  Breeze at 6-8 mph.  Surface water temp at 52 F.  No boat traffic.  Two loons by point.  The lake really looks healthy.
Great day to test! Bright sun- wispy clouds.  Breeze ranging from 2 mph to gusts of 10 mph.  No boat traffic. One loon in the area.
Beautiful sunny clear day.  Very light breeze around 4-5 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons to be seen- although they do have a nest this year.
Totally overcast day.  Wind about 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  One loon in the areal.
Beautiful sunny day with wispy clouds.  Breeze around 3-5 mph.  Some boat traffic.  2 loons in the area.
Sunny day.  Light breeze.  No boat traffic.
Bright sunny afternoon.  Wind out of the southeast at 12 to 15 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons to be seen.

Cloudy day.  Breeze 5 to 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  One juvenile loon.  This will be the last entry for the year.  Lake seems to be clear on the surface but murkier deeper.  I suspect some inversion is starting.  Cloudy day.  Breeze 5 to 8 mph.  No boat traffic.  One juvenile loon.  This will be the last entry for the year.  Lake seems to be clear on the surface but murkier deeper.  I suspect some inversion is starting.
First testing for 2018.  Ice out on May 2- possibly the latest date for the occurrence.  Bright sunny day.  No wind.  No boat traffic.  Two loons returned to the lake on May 5th.
Overcast day. Winds 15 mph. No boat traffic.
Bright sunny day.  No clouds.  Wind around 15 mph- gusting to 20 mph.  Considerable boat traffic.  No loons.
Nice day with hazy clouds.  Wind around 4 to 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  8 loons on the lake in one big group.
Cold crisp day with clear sky and winds around 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  Loons left in early September.  This will be the last entry for Viola Lake for 2018.  Surface temperature is 51 F.
Ice out on April 20th.  First entry for the year.  Mostly cloudy with slight breeze of 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons seen today- but have seen two on the lake this week.
Clear sky and not a breath of wind.  The lake looked like glass.  No boat traffic.  The cottonwood trees were leaving a lot of their cotton on the surface.  No loons seen.

Partly sunny day with wind around 8 to 10 mph.  The lake around the shore has a lot of yellow pine pollen on it making it look murky- but the quality is still quite good.  No boat traffic.  No loons seen while testing.  The lake is starting to thermocline between 15 and 20 feet- with about an 8  F degree differential.  As the lake warms up- the differential will grow substantially with anything below the thermocline not getting above 60 F.  Dissolved oxygen is uniform at saturation down to 15 feet.  At 20 feet the D.O. increases by about 1 ppm because of the temperature change.  At the bottom- D.O. is only 2.3 ppm.
Bright sunny day- wispy clouds breeze 2-3 mph.  A lot of boat traffic.  Two loons on northeast side close to shore.
Sunny- clear day.  No wind. There is boat traffic.  Two loons in the area.
Bright sunny day with almost no clouds.  Wind around 10 mph.  Considerable boat traffic.  No loons to be seen while testing.
Clear day.  No wind.  No boat traffic.  No loons to be seen.
Cloudy day.  Light breeze.  One juvenile loon on the lake.  No boat traffic.

Bright sunny day with wispy clouds.  Strong wind out of the south- maybe 15 mph.  Loons are gone.  No boat traffic.  Looked for freshwater jellyfish but did not see any. This will be the last entry for 2019.
First day of testing in 2020.  Ice out on the lake on April 3rd.  Sunny day with breeze about 5 to 7 mph.  One loon on the lake.  No boat traffic.
Bright sunny day.  Wind around 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  No loons to be seen.
Clear blue sky.  Warm day with very light breeze.  Several boats on the lake.
Bright beautiful morning with clear sky and light breeze less than 5 mph.  Almost no boat traffic.  No loons in the area.
Mostly cloudy with a few patches of sun.  Wind 5-7 mph with gusts up to 10 mph.  No boat traffic.  Two loons in the area.

Sunny clear day with light breeze under 5 mph.  No boat traffic.  The loons have apparently gone for the season.  The freshwater jellyfish have arrived and are in the west end suspended over the deep water.  They can be seen about 2 feet under the surface- about the size of a dime in diameter.

Sunny day with small puffy clouds.  The wind is out of the northwest around 10 mph gusting to 15 mph.  No boat traffic.  One juvenile loon stayed close to the boat all during the testing.  The lake is almost completely uniform in temperature from top to bottom only differing by 1.9 degrees.  Likewise- the  dissolved oxygen is at saturation from top to bogttgom except at 35 feet it drops slightly by 1.5 ppm.  The Secchi reading is also low- so I believe the lake has already gone through its Fall turnover.
